OL,3,CReservist, 55, becomes oldest person
OL,4,Cto complete Nato's toughest challenge
OL,6,FA 55-year-old Scottish army reservist
OL,7,Fis believed to have become the oldest
OL,8,Fperson to complete Nato's toughest
OL,9,Fpatrolling challenge.
OL,11,FMajor David "Harry" Hood, from
OL,12,FDunfermline, earned a bronze medal in
OL,13,Fthe gruelling Exercise Cambrian
OL,14,FPatrol, which sees teams of soldiers
OL,15,Fattempt to navigate a 60km course
OL,16,Fthrough the rugged Brecon Beacons in
OL,17,Funder 48 hours, while carrying 35kg
OL,18,Fpacks.
