OL,3,CReservist, 55, becomes oldest person
OL,4,Cto complete Nato's toughest challenge
OL,6,FHowever just days before the event the
OL,7,Fteam found itself a man down after
OL,8,Fseveral members had to drop out due to
OL,9,Fwork commitments, injuries or illness,
OL,10,Fresulting in Major Hood calling on his
OL,11,Fson ` also a serving soldier ` to step
OL,12,Finto the breach.
OL,14,FMajor Hood said: "We had been training
OL,15,Ffor months, but being reservists and
OL,16,Fgiven how tough the test is, some had
OL,17,Fto drop out. Days before the exercise,
OL,18,Fwe were a man down and couldn't
OL,19,Fcompete ` so that's when I phoned my
OL,20,Fson, Declan."
